        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 9:01AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 900 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles north of Gravette to 3 miles northwest of
Cherokee Landing State Park. Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Adair State Park...               Carrollton...
Rudd...                           Metalton...
Elkins...                         Cincinnati...
Savoy...                          Forum...
Aurora...                         Cave Springs...
Winslow...                        Pleasant Ridge...
Scraper...                        Odell...
Hobbs State Park...               Best...
Lincoln...                        Clifty...
Busch...                          Georgetown...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 41 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for northwestern and
west central Arkansas...and northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
